summary: Ms. Leanne Kinnard is President and Founder of Tech One IT in Phoenix, Arizona.  She also acts as Sr. Vice President of Business Development for Hallmark Global Technologies of which Tech One is a valued member.Ms. Kinnard graduated in 1981 with a Bachelor of Arts in Business Systems Analysis from New Mexico State Universtiy. She possesses over twenty five years experience in Information Technology and the IT consulting and staffing industry. She began her career as a Systems Analyst and then discovered she was passionate about IT consulting.  She entered the IT consulting and contracting industry as a Systems Analyst and then became Account Executive for a national company where she developed her consultative approach to helping clients meet their growing and evolving IT needs.  To this day, she continues to work in partnership with clients to provide technical staffing solutions which consist of total project management and turnkey solutions; to contractors for staff supplementation; and direct hire searches.In 1999, Leanne incorporated Tech One and her company has been a reliable source of IT professionals to the Arizona  marketplace since that time. Leanne’s technical background combined with her experience as an Account Executive, has given her a broadened perspective and unique ability to serve clients while building Tech One. She has hired and retained savvy IT professionals who understand the trends and challenges of IT and also can relate to the needs of IT managers and staff.  Her experience has given her insight into retaining and appreciating the seasoned veterans of the IT business, as well as the recruiting and grooming of tomorrow’s technology leaders and innovators.Specialties: Tech One’s consulting practice is specialized in providing Project Managers and Business Analysts.  Tech One’s portfolio consists of many successful IT engagements in the following areas:  .net, SAP, Peoplesoft, Asset Management, Business Intelligence, Organizational Development, IT Governance, Product Data Management (PDM), IT Security and Audit, Systems Administration, Mainframe legacy, Informix, Oracle, Tivoli, Veritos, SANs, Java, Agile, Ajax, Flex and many  other emerging technologies.
